Service Principal Name		-		SPN is a unique identifier of a service instance. SPN is used by Kerberos to associate a service instance with a service logon account, e.g. nfs/server1.example.com@TRANSPOWER.CO.NZ or HTTP/server2.example.com@AARNET.EDU.AU\
