Service Principal Name\
 - a unique identifier of a service instance offerred by a particular host within an authentication domain\
 - SPN is used by Kerberos authentication to associate a service instance with a service logon account\
 - this allows a client application to request that the service authenticate an account even if the client does not have the account name\
